From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Peter van der Perk <peter.vanderperk@nxp.com>
Date: Wed, 17 Jun 2026 09:00:00 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] imx95: navq: fix SPL DDR address not covered by MMU map

In lf-6.18.y a new spl_enable_caches() was added in arch_cpu_init().
It places MMU page tables at CFG_SYS_SECURE_SDRAM_BASE and enables the
D-cache. The iMX95 EVK config defines:

  CFG_SYS_SECURE_SDRAM_BASE = 0x8A000000
  CFG_SYS_SECURE_SDRAM_SIZE = 0x06000000  (covers 0x8A000000-0x90000000)

The NavQ SPL is loaded into DDR at 0x88240000 for the lpboot/SCMI path
(CONFIG_SPL_TEXT_BASE=0x88240000). This address lies below
CFG_SYS_SECURE_SDRAM_BASE and is therefore NOT covered by any memory
map entry. When the MMU is enabled the CPU immediately takes a
translation fault executing from the unmapped SPL text region.

Fix: for TARGET_IMX95_NAVQA/B extend the secure DDR window down to
0x88000000 so it covers the SPL text (0x88240000), stack/BSS
(0x88296000) and leaves 576 KB below the SPL for the page tables placed
by spl_enable_caches(). The EVK default is unchanged.

Upstream-Status: Inappropriate [NavQ platform specific]
Signed-off-by: Peter van der Perk <peter.vanderperk@nxp.com>
---
--- a/include/configs/imx95_evk.h
+++ b/include/configs/imx95_evk.h
@@ -23,8 +23,18 @@
 #define PHYS_SDRAM_2_SIZE		0x380000000 /* 14GB */
 #endif
 
-#define CFG_SYS_SECURE_SDRAM_BASE	0x8A000000 /* Secure DDR region for A55, SPL could use first 2MB */
+#if defined(CONFIG_TARGET_IMX95_NAVQA) || defined(CONFIG_TARGET_IMX95_NAVQB)
+/* NavQ SPL runs from DDR at 0x88240000 (lpboot/SCMI path). Extend the
+ * secure DDR window to cover the SPL text so the MMU map set up by
+ * spl_enable_caches() in arch_cpu_init() does not leave the SPL address
+ * in an unmapped region, which would cause an immediate translation fault.
+ */
+#define CFG_SYS_SECURE_SDRAM_BASE	0x88000000
+#define CFG_SYS_SECURE_SDRAM_SIZE	0x08000000	/* 0x88000000-0x90000000 */
+#else
+#define CFG_SYS_SECURE_SDRAM_BASE	0x8A000000	/* Secure DDR region for A55, SPL could use first 2MB */
 #define CFG_SYS_SECURE_SDRAM_SIZE	0x06000000
+#endif
 
 #define WDOG_BASE_ADDR			WDG3_BASE_ADDR
 
